Uighur burkas banned by Beijing to halt extremists | The Times

The authorities in the capital of China’s Xinjiang region are to ban muslim 
women from wearing burqas as the Communist leadership grows more panicked by 
the threat of Islamic extremism and intensifies efforts to quell rising 
ethnic violence.


The announcement, which follows earlier bans on women’s face coverings and 
men’s beards in smaller cities of Xinjiang, reflects Beijing’s deepening 
unease over the stability of the muslim Uighur population concentrated in 
the far west.


